node.text:
Three takeaways:
1. Fran is *never* “Friendly” 🤪
2. Run through the finish line before you sprawl out on the floor.
3. No matter how well you executed a workout, you’re always going to say you think you could’ve gone faster 🙃 That’s why we love CrossFit am I right- always improvements to be made 😈
•••
🎥: @jtwiseguy

node.text:
Things I’ve been doing to keep me distracted during this rest period of elbow recovery: morning walks in the Malibu mountains, binge watching Outer Banks & Manifest, chillin with the goats & pig, coffee on the beach, a mandatory afternoon nap every day, petting horses, Dodgers game, sunset dinners.

Things I cannot do; fix my hair (ever tried a ponytail with one hand.. you can’t 😜), eat with a fork without making a mess (handhelds are preferred), drive, opening things is hard! I’m super independent, so feeling this dependent doing basic things has taught me patience.

Fitness wise, I have done absolutely nothing since the injury. It’s been amazing to let my body & mind have some time off. The most I have done is go for a couple mile walk. I plan to start easing back into bike erging next week just for the sake of feeling better & like I’m in more of a routine.

A few silver linings are being able to spend time with my mom as she is helping me do things I can’t, a nice extended stay in Malibu, & meeting new people who are now friends through this process. Excited to keep growing this list 🤍

I got my cast off on Thursday & began PT. The progress is addicting & I am extremely motivated to make this the strongest elbow ever! I plan to stay in Malibu for at least another 2 weeks to work with this physical therapist. So drop some LA area recommendations below 👇🏼 Love y’all 💓

Here are some of the photos that were taken for the thumbnail that didn’t get selected. Thank you to everyone who tagged me in posts that week, I loved seeing you getting after it!!! 🤩💪🏼✨

On the mend 👍🏼
Woke up from surgery in a lot of pain, but doing better & I’m very happy to get this part over with. My doctor said everything went perfect which is a huge relief. (For specifics on my injury read my most recent post)

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by Brooke Wells on August 11, 2021 tagging @nobull. May be an image of 1 person and indoor.

node.text:
💪🏻 ELBOW UPDATE 💪🏻

It’s been a whirlwind since my elbow injury last week at the CrossFit Games. Thank you so much to everyone who continues to check on me, offer recommendations, or wish me good luck.

Immediately after the Games, I received an MRI at the hospital in Madison. The images were passed on to experts who work with other professional athletes and understand the demand competitive CrossFit requires of my body.

Although the results were not what I hoped to hear, the consistency among their feedback gives me confidence. 

There is a complete tear of the muscle and ligaments on the inner side of the elbow (UCL), which caused the dislocation. A high-grade tear of the lateral collateral, and the flexer tendon was pulled of the bone. There was no fracture, or no surface damage to the joint. 

Through a thorough process, my team and I have identified the doctor that who will complete reconstructive surgery (Tommy-John) to stabilize my elbow, along with tendon flexor surgery. All the doctors who reviewed my injury expect a FULL RECOVERY. 

This has been a lot to process, with plenty of emotions. But above all I’m anxious and excited to finally get my elbow FIXED, so I can get back to doing what I love. I’m staying positive and love your support so much!! I’ll continue to provide updates as available.

node.text:
Wow. 2021 Games season. Definitely the most bittersweet year I have ever endured. It absolutely did not end the way I had ever hoped or imagined with an injury that ended my competition, but to see the unconditional support & love from the community, my team & my family was something so very special that I will never forget 🥺🤍

Thank you @nobull @crossfitgames for putting on such an amazing event. It was SO GOOD TO BE BACK in Madison 🤩 surrounded by the community again 🥰 Thank you to everyone who cheered & supported us athletes, whether that was in the stadium or at home. 🙏🏼 a huge thank you to the judges, volunteers & staff for all your hard work! 💓 and to the *medical staff* who put me back in one piece. I hope & wish no one has to rely on them like I had to, but there is no better team to ensure your safety- thank you!!!

MY @prvnfitness TEAM, @tiaclair1 @shaneorr01 @nicjohnstonn @willmoorad @dwight.upshaw. We worked harder than ever during training, while also enjoying every minute of it (okay maybe not every minute 🥴😂). I love this team so freaking much. They have my back no matter what. 💕

Thank you to my agents, family & friends for the cheers while things were going amazing, and the endless care & support during a very tough time 🤍 @industrytodd @okeefmr @drobbins95 @loudlivesports @sydneywells @lisalynnwells @charwellss #dad

A massive thank you to my sponsors who have showed so much love & support. 💖 I genuinely love each company so much. @nobull @beam @gowod_mobilityfirst @1stphorm @whoop @macrostax @performasleep @compexusa

Thank you to my CrossFit gyms who put up with me daily 🥴🤍 @crossfiteastnashville @crossfittrivium

THANK YOU TO EVERYONE WHO HAS BEEN A PART OF MY JOURNEY 🥺 I have been trying to read all my messages & I appreciate them so much 🙏🏼 This is just a part of my story, and we are FAR from finished 🤍

node.text:
Thank you for the overwhelming messages of support. 🙏🏼 There is no community like this and although I am heartbroken, I’m thriving off your energy and love. 🤍

Last night I dislocated my elbow during the max snatch event, and was forced to medically withdrawal.

I dedicated my life to being prepared for this years CrossFit Games and I’m absolutely the fittest I’ve ever been. To not be able to fight for a podium spot today crushes me, but I’ll be back. 

Thank you to the extremely professional medical staff that treated me on-site. This is a speedbump and it’s all part of my journey. Gods plan is bigger than mine. See you soon. 💓
